  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cotton farmers are increasingly vulnerable to climate change, with shorter rainy seasons and the need for crop diversifications. This project will aim to reduce vulnerability to climate change by working with hundreds of cotton cooperatives. It will aim to explore how cotton farmers can diversify their crops to those that both generate local food needs as well as local and regional markets. It will look carefully at the impact of climate change on women. As a result, cotton producers will have greater food and income security over the long term</narrative>
